name: Bale Kulkul Bali
address: Jalan Piakan No.18, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: I got to know this place from one of the famous travel agents and was recommended by my driver.  When I arrived here the place was comfortable and peaceful far from the bustling city of Bali.  What is unfortunate is that the prices listed on the travel agent with those listed on the spot are very different.  I also compared with the tourist who also took the photo package here but they got a much cheaper price than what was set in this Bale Kulkul.  Please check the price first before coming here.
review 2:
Great memories to dress Indonesian style. They stuff is kind but the photographer was kind in a hurry and to so professional. Worth giving a try!
They have also a restaurant!
review 3: I came for some Hipmi Seminar. Not many things can found here. Big parking area anyway. Staff and food average
review 4: Very nice place. The food is nice. Recommended place. They offer traditional balinese clothes for taking pictures.
review 5: photo shoot in Bali‚Äôs traditional wear

review 3: An alternative in Celuk area, which considerably "dry". Food is OK, and price is modest.

review 5: Very friendly staff. Food was good as well as the quantity.  It was pleasant & peaceful to go to during the hot afternoon.!

name: Warung Makan Samania
address: Melati 7 No.10, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80237, Indonesia
review 1:
After kecak dance at 730pm, we search about the nearby restaurant and Google recommend this.

We are not from local, so it's a bit worry about the hygiene and food taste, fortunately everything fit our needs. Food taste good, we ordered pork rib set and seafood set, sufficient for 5 adults. Food serving very fast, just that no one at yhe front desk when wanna make payment. üòÖ

They do have a kid play area near the garden which my 3yo boy enjoy his time before the food served. Play area is simple and clean.
review 2:
Not so recommended.
Our first time to visit the restaurant and only two of us at that time in the restaurant for lunch but we have to wait more than 45 minutes only for two food order.
I was ordering Iga Bakar Babi and my wife was ordering Paket C (ikan bakar,kerang) and both orders were average for taste.
review 3:
The food is great, and the portion is just perfect. My favorite menu is Gurame Nyat Nyat, which is tasteful.

Service is nice. Sometimes, nobody is visible at the front desk, so you have to find them in the back area.

Atmosphere is so so. Some tables are sested; they got lesehan (seated on the floor type thing); and some tables in the garden sector.

There is a playground around the corner that works for kids under 6 yo.

Its parking lot could fit 2 cars and some scooters.

Recommended!
review 4: Great food with affordable price. Good environment for hangout also work. Family and kid friendly zone
review 5: The food was great and place so friendly also the owner very humble and welcome ..we have a  good lunch there and we will be back again soon for seafood trial ..good luck and wishing more visitor recommended place to have a good food with family and friends üíù

review 1: Nice little street cafe! One of not many in Celuk that is open in the early morning! And they have a good coffee machine and a skilled barista. No breakfast available snacks only. Thank you!
review 2: Amazing cafe, a hidden gem in Batubulan. Excellent coffee with a long tradition. Pleasant sitting, nice employees. I highly recommend it to all coffee lovers.
review 3: Great coffee close to Kecak nearby! Piccolo banana was different but tasty. Lattes were pretty good too.
review 5: Very Nice coffee was served even though the shop is small.  Interior and ambience was very good. Very rare good coffee spots in the location.

name: Taman Ayu Luwak Coffee
address: Sukawati, Batubulan, Kec. Sukawati, Kabupaten Gianyar, Bali 80582, Indonesia
review 1: We had such a lovely tour around the plantations. Dwi showed us around and had so much knowledge of the processes and benefits of the products. She is so friendly! We had a lovely tasting with a nice view. Also bought some products in the shop.
review 2:
First time for me to visit this place only with my tour guide - Pak Made. He knows that I really like coffee but want to try something different other than normal cafe and we came to this place. I can say this  most likely a coffee sanctuary where we can see from the beginning / first step, coffee bean being treated until served to you. One of the most expensive and legendary for a coffee is Luwak Coffee Wild from Kintamani (they even have Luwak - live animal but only for research purposes, the coffee it self being collected from small forest/garden by the farmer).  on this place you also can see how Balinese people try to roast the coffee manually using fire stove with the wood as a fuel and earthenware to roadt the coffee, with small fire You will only need to pay 60,000 IDR, in order to taste it. Other than that, we can enjoy this coffee in small gazebo next to the river and a pura (a holy place for hinduism to do praying). Really peaceful and love much enjoying that such of experience.

You will also be served to taste around 12 small cups consist of coffee and tea, and after that if you like it you can buy at their small store. You can pay it cash or buy using Card. If not wrong, this place also have such a room to stay overnight but r di not have detail info yet about it. Overall, really love the situation/ambience, love the taste of the Wild Luwak Coffee Kintamani and also arabica kintamani, love how the way the serve and for sure I recommend to come to this place, if you want try something different on how to enjoy the coffee in the different ambience üôèüèª
review 3: I've always wanted to try Kopi Luwak and finally got the chance to when we visited Taman Ayu. Their place is very lush and green with so many of their ingredients grown right on the premises. Ayu, our guide, gave us a tour of the place explaining all that goes on and into making their teas and coffees. They have quite a variety of teas and coffee which can be bought from their little store. Not much else to do though, but I liked what they had on offer.
review 4: The staff are extremely kind and caring and you can even have a memorable swing! The coffee is delicious. Thank you very much üôè
review 5: Looking for great taste of luwak coffee? This place are really good and high recomended, they provide free testing of any kind of herbal tea and bali coffee... Really enjoyedüòä
